cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.CR 

This paper discusses the use of precision-recall curves in machine learning, which is a common topic in the subfield of machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the implications of the unachievable region in precision-recall space on empirical evaluation methodology, which is relevant to information retrieval (cs.IR), computer vision (cs.CV), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and cryptography (cs.CR) subfields. However, since the focus is on machine learning, cs.LG is the most likely sub-category.
